    Variables: They are meant to store value.

    1. dataType variableName=value; [ If you know the exact value]

    DataTypes:
       1. Primitive Data Type
       a) You don't need any object to be able to use them
       b) Primitive data types occupy pre-defined fixed memory spaces
          byte, short, int, long, float, double, char, boolean

    2. dataType variableName; [When we don't know the exact value at that time]
       variableName=value;

       2. Non-Primitive Data Types
              a) You need object to be able to use them
              b) Non-Primitive data types does not occupy pre-defined fixed memory spaces
                 Arrays, collections, String...
                 int numbers[] = new int[];
